---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Disney Deception — Nazaryah"
  description="The ancient gods hiding inside the stories we hand to our children — traced from Babel to the box office."
>
  <div class="sw-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="sw-hero">
      <p class="sw-label">&#8213; A Critical Examination &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="sw-title">The Disney Deception</h1>
      <p class="sw-sub">
        The ancient gods hiding inside the stories we hand to our children
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          Every classic Disney story has a pedigree. Walt did not invent Cinderella, Snow White, Hercules, or the Little Mermaid. He rebranded them. Behind each sanitized musical number stands an ancient myth, and behind each ancient myth stands a pagan worship system — most of them looping back to the same fertility goddess, the same sun god, and the same rebellion that began at the Tower of Babel.
        </p>
        <p>
          Modern parents hand these films to their children as innocent entertainment. They are anything but. The word "occult" simply means <em>hidden</em>, and Disney is a masterclass in hiding ancient deity worship inside animation cells, songs, and merchandise. The "magic" is not metaphorical in the way parents assume it is — the symbols, the rituals, the bloodlines, the themes, and the founder himself all carry fingerprints that would horrify any believer who bothered to look.
        </p>
        <p>
          Scripture is not silent on this. Yahuah warned Israel not to learn the ways of the nations, "for every abomination to Yahuah, which He hates, have they done unto their gods" (Deuteronomy 12:31). He commanded that the names of other gods not even be mentioned from the mouth of His people (Exodus 23:13). Disney does not merely mention them — Disney animates them, sings them, merchandises them, and builds theme parks around them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── CASTLE, STAR, AND WISH ── -->
    <section class="sw-section sw-section-alt">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p class="sw-section-heading">The Castle, the Star, and the Wish</p>
        <p>
          Even the Disney logo itself is a confession. The castle is the image of the mystery-religion fortress, and the star that arcs over it every time a film begins is not innocent decoration. "When You Wish Upon a Star" is the Disney corporate anthem — and it is, word for word, a prayer to the host of heaven.
        </p>
        <div class="sw-scripture-block">
          <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Deuteronomy 4:19</p>
          <p>"And lest thou lift up thine eyes unto heaven, and when thou seest the sun, and the moon, and the stars, even all the host of heaven, shouldest be driven to worship them, and serve them..."</p>
        </div>
        <p>
          Yahuah named this specific practice and forbade it. Disney built its brand identity around it. Children are taught from infancy that the stars hear them, grant their desires, and guide their destiny. That is not a harmless bedtime song. It is astral worship with a melody.
        </p>
        <p class="sw-section-heading">The Man Behind the Mouse</p>
        <p>
          Walt Disney himself was documented as a member of DeMolay — a Masonic youth organization — and was later inducted into its Legion of Honor. His parks are dense with occult symbolism for those who know how to read it: the obelisks, the pyramids, the all-seeing eye motifs, the pentagrams hidden in the layout of his plazas. This is not speculation; it is documented history the Disney corporation itself does not deny.
        </p>
        <p>
          The question every believer must face is this: if Yahuah forbade the very mention of these gods, what does it mean that we have welcomed their stories, their symbols, and their songs into our homes — and taught our children to love them?
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── STORY BUTTONS ── -->
    <section class="sw-cta-section">
      <p class="sw-cta-label">&#8213; Choose Your Study &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-cta-title">The Stories, One at a Time</h2>
      <p class="sw-cta-sub">
        Each page below traces a Disney figure back to its pre-Christian root. The same handful of deities keep surfacing under different names.
      </p>

      <div class="sw-symbol-grid">

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <a href="/disney/mermaid" class="sw-btn-link">The Little Mermaid &nbsp;&#8594;</a>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">Atargatis, the Syrian fish-goddess, and the cult Yahuah condemned</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Cinderella</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">A solar myth — the slipper, the midnight transformation, the harvest goddess</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Snow White</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">The Isis-Osiris death-and-resurrection pattern in German folklore</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Sleeping Beauty</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">The Persephone cycle from Eleusis — the maiden, the frozen world, the spring</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">The Lion King</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">The Osiris-Horus-Set myth told almost line-for-line</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Moana</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">Polynesian sea-goddess worship — Maui is not a fictional character</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Frozen</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">Skadi, the Norse ice-goddess, rebranded — and the theme of self-deification</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Pocahontas</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">Pantheistic nature-worship set to music — a catechism against Genesis 1</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sw-sym-group">
          <span class="sw-btn-soon">Hercules</span>
          <p class="sw-sym-note">Undisguised Greek polytheism — Zeus as a loving father, Olympus as heaven</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── QUOTE ── -->
    <section class="sw-footer-quote">
      <p class="sw-quote-text">"Come out of her, my people, that ye be not partakers of her sins, and that ye receive not of her plagues."</p>
      <p class="sw-quote-ref">— Revelation 18:4</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .sw-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #060810 0%, #0c1020 20%, #080c18 100%);
    color: #f0e0bf;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .sw-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a2448;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%, rgba(30, 50, 160, 0.2), transparent 70%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #040610 0%, #0c1020 100%);
  }

  .sw-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #4a5888;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sw-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 3.8rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .sw-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    color: #c4a46b;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .sw-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #101830;
  }

  .sw-section-alt {
    background: rgba(10, 20, 60, 0.15);
  }

  .sw-prose {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #d9c9a8;
  }

  .sw-prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .sw-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .sw-prose em { color: #c4a46b; font-style: italic; }

  .sw-section-heading {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: #c4a46b;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem !important;
  }

  .sw-scripture-block {
    border-left: 2px solid #1E3A8B;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
    background: rgba(10, 20, 80, 0.15);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .sw-scripture-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: #3A5AAA;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;
  }

  /* ── CTA SECTION ── */
  .sw-cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #101830;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 50%, rgba(20, 40, 100, 0.15), transparent 70%);
  }

  .sw-cta-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #3a4870;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sw-cta-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.1rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .sw-cta-sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #c4ad84;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Symbol grid ── */
  .sw-symbol-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 2rem 2.5rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .sw-sym-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    width: 240px;
  }

  .sw-sym-note {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 8.5px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: #3a4868;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 0.65rem;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .sw-btn-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.6rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #f5e8c8;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a3a9a 0%, #102880 50%, #081850 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(60, 100, 186, 0.4);
    border-radius: 32px 32px 26px 26px / 18px 18px 32px 32px;
    box-shadow:
      0 4px 16px rgba(20, 50, 140, 0.2),
      inset 0 2px 4px rgba(100, 150, 220, 0.25),
      inset 0 -2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .sw-btn-link:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #2a4aba 0%, #1a3a9a 50%, #10286e 100%);
    color: #fff5e0;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow:
      0 8px 20px rgba(20, 50, 140, 0.35),
      inset 0 2px 4px rgba(120, 170, 240, 0.3),
      inset 0 -2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  }

  .sw-btn-soon {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.6rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #3a4868;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #080c18 0%, #060810 100%);
    border: 1px solid #141c38;
    border-radius: 32px 32px 26px 26px / 18px 18px 32px 32px;
    cursor: default;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* ── Footer quote ── */
  .sw-footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #080c18 0%, #040608 100%);
  }

  .sw-quote-text {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    font-style: italic;
    color: #c4a46b;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .sw-quote-ref {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: #2a3858;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .sw-symbol-grid { gap: 1.5rem; }
    .sw-sym-group { width: 200px; }
  }
</style>
